---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Notes"
  description="Technical notes and essays by Daniel Edmund Rochatka on software architecture, AI systems, product engineering, knowledge, and research."
>
  <section class="page-intro section-pad">
    <p class="eyebrow">Notes</p>
    <h1>Technical arguments, design reasoning, and ideas before they become projects.</h1>
    <p>This section is intentionally prepared but not padded with placeholder articles. Notes will appear when there is a complete argument worth preserving.</p>
  </section>
  <section class="empty-state section-pad rule-top">
    <div class="empty-number">00</div>
    <div>
      <h2>No published notes yet.</h2>
      <p>The initial site establishes a durable publishing structure without pretending that unfinished drafts are finished work.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
